  "title": "Response to Comment on: The ORIGIN Trial Investigators. Characteristics Associated With Maintenance of Mean A1C &amp;lt;6.5% in People With Dysglycemia in the ORIGIN Trial. Diabetes Care 2013;36:2915–2922",
  "abstract": "We thank Drs. Esposito and Giugliano for their interest in the glycemic control results from ORIGIN (Outcome Reduction with Initial Glargine Intervention) (1), and their recognition of the potential importance of our findings. Citing their own systematic reviews of literature, they point out that the ability of insulin treatment to attain good control of A1C levels is strongly related to the level of glycemic control at which the intervention begins (2). We agree that starting treatment with insulin glargine for study participants with overt diabetes at entry in ORIGIN was able to keep A1C below 7.0% …",
